{"word":"ἔμφρων","slug":"ἔμφρων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔμφρων</b></el> <el>(ἔμ-φρων, ονος,) </el>n (e)m-fr wn_onos) <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἐν, φρήν</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>in one's mind</i> or <i>senses</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>alive</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>rational, intelligent</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>sensible, shrewd, prudent</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}